{"questionId":"5627","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A mixture of 1.00 mol SO<sub>2</sub>(g), 2.00 mol O<sub>2</sub>(g) and 1.00 mol SO<sub>3</sub>(g) is placed in a 1.00 dm<sup>3</sup>&nbsp;container and allowed to reach equilibrium.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">2SO<sub>2</sub>(g) + O<sub>2</sub>(g) <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\rightleftharpoons \">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇌</mo>\n</math></span>&nbsp;2SO<sub>3</sub>(g)</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The equilibrium constant, <em>K</em><sub>c</sub>, is 0.282 at temperature T.</p>\n<p>Deduce, showing your work, the direction of the initial reaction.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>«</strong><em>Q</em>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{{[{\\text{S}}{{\\text{O}}_3}]}^2}}}{{{{[{\\text{S}}{{\\text{O}}_2}]}^2}[{{\\text{O}}_2}]}} = \\frac{{{{1.00}^2}}}{{{{1.00}^2} \\times 2.00}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>S</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <msub>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mtext>O</mtext>\n                </mrow>\n                <mn>3</mn>\n              </msub>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo>\n            <mrow>\n              <mtext>S</mtext>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <msub>\n                <mrow>\n                  <mtext>O</mtext>\n                </mrow>\n                <mn>2</mn>\n              </msub>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msub>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>O</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msub>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>1.00</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>1.00</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>2.00</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span><strong>» =</strong>&nbsp;0.500</p>\n<p>reverse reaction favoured/reaction proceeds to the left <strong><em>AND</em></strong>&nbsp;<em>Q </em>&gt; <em>K</em><sub>c</sub>/0.500 &gt; 0.282</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Do </em><strong><em>not </em></strong><em>award M2 without M1.</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"5627","referenceCode":"18M.2.sl.TZ2.5b","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"The equilibrium constant, Kc, is 0.282 at temperature T. Deduce, showing your work, the direction of the initial reaction.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 7: Equilibrium","7.1 Equilibrium","Core","Topic 7: Equilibrium"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}